01:39:21,621 --> 01:39:24,226
and everything's
gonna turn out fine.

2025
01:39:26,226 --> 01:39:32,498
<i>Chaz: And the first day or
two he looked in the mirror,</i>

2026
01:39:32,499 --> 01:39:35,770
<i>he was very pleased
with what he saw.</i>

2027
01:39:36,770 --> 01:39:39,638
<i>But just like
all the other surgeries,</i>

2028
01:39:39,639 --> 01:39:41,140
<i>there was an infection</i>

2029
01:39:41,141 --> 01:39:43,811
<i>and they had to undo everything.</i>

2030
01:39:44,811 --> 01:39:48,580
<i>That left him
more debilitated than ever,</i>

2031
01:39:48,581 --> 01:39:52,151
<i>and he just decided
no more surgeries.</i>

2032
01:39:52,152 --> 01:39:54,622
<i>No more.</i>

2033
01:39:55,622 --> 01:39:58,257
<i>Roger's not one
to look back and say,</i>

2034
01:39:58,258 --> 01:40:01,393
<i>"Oh, coulda,
woulda, shoulda."</i>

2035
01:40:01,394 --> 01:40:03,662
But there were times
when he wrote a note

2036
01:40:03,663 --> 01:40:05,597
that said,

2037
01:40:05,598 --> 01:40:07,800
"Kill me."

2038
01:40:07,801 --> 01:40:10,536
I mean, I have that note.

2039
01:40:10,537 --> 01:40:12,671
"Kill me."

2040
01:40:12,672 --> 01:40:16,479
And I said, "No. No."

2041
01:40:19,479 --> 01:40:23,327
I told him
that was not an option.

2042
01:40:34,129 --> 01:40:37,229
<i>Female aide: Oh, you want to walk
until there, or you wanna...?</i>

2043
01:40:37,230 --> 01:40:38,664
<i>Okay.</i>

2044
01:40:38,665 --> 01:40:42,572
But you know, getting
over there, over that bump...

2045
01:40:45,572 --> 01:40:49,241
Okay, who's gonna help him
stand to go up to the stairs?

2046
01:40:49,242 --> 01:40:51,310
I know he wants
to write instructions.

2047
01:40:51,311 --> 01:40:53,245
Chaz:
Do you want the walker?

2048
01:40:53,246 --> 01:40:55,147
Yes or no,
do you want the walker?

2049
01:40:55,148 --> 01:40:57,816
No. Okay, then let's get...

2050
01:40:57,817 --> 01:41:00,589
Yeah, but we have
to get up and get going.

2051
01:41:02,589 --> 01:41:05,357
<i>Chaz: People would say,
"Ah, don't you get tired?"</i>

2052
01:41:05,358 --> 01:41:06,892
You have to trust us.

2053
01:41:06,893 --> 01:41:09,628
<i>You have to trust that
we know what we're doing.</i>

2054
01:41:09,629 --> 01:41:11,463
<i>Chaz:
Yeah, I get tired sometimes.</i>

2055
01:41:11,464 --> 01:41:14,166
"Move this chair
so it faces stairs."

2056
01:41:14,167 --> 01:41:17,503
You know, no, no, guess what,
it's a few steps.

2057
01:41:17,504 --> 01:41:20,672
You can get out of the chair
and you can walk up the stairs.

2058
01:41:20,673 --> 01:41:22,908
That's what you've
been practicing every day.

2059
01:41:22,909 --> 01:41:24,610
You can do this.

2060
01:41:24,611 --> 01:41:27,146
<i>Chaz:
But I never got so tired</i>

2061
01:41:27,147 --> 01:41:28,514
<i>that I wanted to give up.</i>

2062
01:41:28,515 --> 01:41:30,449
Come on, Uncle Roger.

2063
01:41:30,450 --> 01:41:31,884
Chaz:
No, he's not gonna do that.

2064
01:41:31,885 --> 01:41:33,519
Let me handle it, please.

2065
01:41:33,520 --> 01:41:35,888
I'm gonna pull
the chair out of the way.

2066
01:41:35,889 --> 01:41:38,290
<i>Chaz: There's so many
people out there</i>

2067
01:41:38,291 --> 01:41:41,693
<i>taking care of people
who are sick or disabled.</i>

2068
01:41:41,694 --> 01:41:45,864
We all go through
the whole gamut of emotions.

2069
01:41:45,865 --> 01:41:48,767
Two, three, up...

2070
01:41:48,768 --> 01:41:50,435
Okay, now hold.

2071
01:41:50,436 --> 01:41:51,837
<i>Flaum: You know, it's
been a long road.</i>

2072
01:41:51,838 --> 01:41:53,939
<i>- I think it's hard.
- Aide: All right.</i>

2073
01:41:53,940 --> 01:41:57,746
It's always been hard,
but it's even harder now.

2074
01:41:59,746 --> 01:42:02,181
<i>Flaum:
He calls her my angel.</i>

2075
01:42:02,182 --> 01:42:03,649
<i>And he means it.</i>

2076
01:42:03,650 --> 01:42:06,652
Chaz: Valentine's Day
wreath I got for you.

2077
01:42:06,653 --> 01:42:08,926
<i>Chaz: Aw.</i>

2078
01:42:12,926 --> 01:42:15,327
<i>Roger: This woman
never lost her love.</i>

2079
01:42:15,328 --> 01:42:16,828
Now do you want to go upstairs?

2080
01:42:16,829 --> 01:42:19,765
<i>She was always there
believing I could do it.</i>

2081
01:42:19,766 --> 01:42:23,902
<i>And her love was like a wind
pushing me back from the grave.</i>

2082
01:42:23,903 --> 01:42:27,839
<i>Chaz: And I told him
that if you promise me</i>

2083
01:42:27,840 --> 01:42:30,442
<i>that you will give it your all,</i>

2084
01:42:30,443 --> 01:42:34,313
<i>I promise you
that I will try to make life</i>

2085
01:42:34,314 --> 01:42:36,215
<i>as interesting
for you as possible...</i>

2086
01:42:36,216 --> 01:42:37,616
<i>( audience applauds )</i>

2087
01:42:37,617 --> 01:42:39,551
<i>...so that every day,</i>

2088
01:42:39,552 --> 01:42:43,824
<i>you have something
to look forward to.</i>

2089
01:42:44,824 --> 01:42:48,762
How does it feel
to be back in your own chair?

2090
01:42:49,762 --> 01:42:51,230
<i>Okay.</i>

2091
01:42:51,231 --> 01:42:52,664
Today is a big day,

2092
01:42:52,665 --> 01:42:56,902
coming home after two months
is very difficult.

2093
01:42:56,903 --> 01:42:58,704
<i>It's a joy,</i>

2094
01:42:58,705 --> 01:43:01,409
but it's also very stressful.

2095
01:43:03,409 --> 01:43:04,843
( laughs )

2096
01:43:04,844 --> 01:43:07,779
<i>- "Especially for you."
- ( laughing )</i>

2097
01:43:07,780 --> 01:43:09,881
<i>Is tha... Are you trying
to be a smart alec?</i>

2098
01:43:09,882 --> 01:43:12,355
<i>Are you trying
to be a smart alec?</i>

2099
01:43:14,955 --> 01:43:17,589
<i>Gregory Nava: We have a saying
in the Latino community,</i>

2100
01:43:17,590 --> 01:43:19,391
<i>"Make your heart your face."</i>

2101
01:43:19,392 --> 01:43:22,394
Oh, now.
Aw, okay.

2102
01:43:22,395 --> 01:43:24,930
<i>Nava: More than anybody
I have ever known,</i>

2103
01:43:24,931 --> 01:43:27,699
<i>his heart is his face.</i>

2104
01:43:27,700 --> 01:43:29,868
That photograph
that was on the cover

2105
01:43:29,869 --> 01:43:31,970
of Esquire says it all.

2106
01:43:31,971 --> 01:43:34,539
<i>This is me. Right?</i>

2107
01:43:34,540 --> 01:43:37,509
<i>And I want you to know</i>

2108
01:43:37,510 --> 01:43:39,911
<i>who I am
and what I'm going through.</i>

2109
01:43:39,912 --> 01:43:41,712
<i>Computerized voice:
I may have things</i>

2110
01:43:42,015 --> 01:43:43,615
<i>to be depressed about,</i>

2111
01:43:43,616 --> 01:43:45,019
<i>but I am not depressed.</i>

2112
01:43:46,019 --> 01:43:48,487
<i>My life seems full again.</i>

2113
01:43:48,488 --> 01:43:50,756
<i>Josh Golden:
Here we are full screen,</i>

2114
01:43:50,757 --> 01:43:52,758
<i>as we start
to bring the screen size down,</i>

2115
01:43:52,759 --> 01:43:55,661
<i>eventually getting
towards iPhone size,</i>

2116
01:43:55,662 --> 01:43:57,896
it's gonna drop,
it's gonna break.

2117
01:43:57,897 --> 01:43:59,431
And now, look at this...

2118
01:43:59,432 --> 01:44:02,634
<i>Computerized voice: My attention
is focused on my new website,</i>

2119
01:44:02,635 --> 01:44:05,570
<i>which will provide a home
for my life's work</i>

2120
01:44:05,571 --> 01:44:07,842
<i>and has an enduring life
of its own.</i>

2121
01:44:09,842 --> 01:44:12,544
"Josh, this is beyond
my wildest dreams."

2122
01:44:12,545 --> 01:44:15,080
Well, I'm glad.
I like to make you happy.

2123
01:44:15,081 --> 01:44:17,783
<i>Golden: Roger has been
ahead of the curve,</i>

2124
01:44:17,784 --> 01:44:21,453
becoming an early and massive
adopter of social media.

2125
01:44:21,454 --> 01:44:24,456
He has almost
800,000 followers on Twitter

2126
01:44:24,457 --> 01:44:25,891
and 100,000 followers
on Facebook.

2127
01:44:25,892 --> 01:44:28,794
"Nice links to IMDB
and Wikipedia."

2128
01:44:28,795 --> 01:44:30,929
<i>Golden: If you look at the
other people how have</i>

2129
01:44:30,930 --> 01:44:35,032
<i>like 850,000 Twitter followers,
it's like Kardashians.</i>

2130
01:44:35,033 --> 01:44:37,402
<i>Golden ( in room ):
Beyond the search widget...</i>

2131
01:44:37,403 --> 01:44:40,939
<i>Rosenbaum: Right now, there's
an argument about the internet.</i>

2132
01:44:40,940 --> 01:44:44,643
<i>Some people say
film criticism is at the end,</i>

2133
01:44:44,644 --> 01:44:46,912
<i>the art of cinema is at the end.</i>

2134
01:44:46,913 --> 01:44:49,681
<i>Roger sees it
in a much more positive way.</i>

2135
01:44:49,682 --> 01:44:51,450
It's a renaissance.

2136
01:44:51,451 --> 01:44:54,986
It's a renaissance of film
appreciation and film criticism.

2137
01:44:54,987 --> 01:44:57,689
<i>The roving reporters
that he uses,</i>

2138
01:44:57,690 --> 01:45:00,091
<i>like on his blog, for example,</i>

2139
01:45:00,092 --> 01:45:01,626
<i>is giving a cortical birth</i>

2140
01:45:01,627 --> 01:45:04,062
<i>to lots of other points of view.</i>

2141
01:45:04,063 --> 01:45:07,833
The passionate fan-culture,
or movie geek culture,

2142
01:45:07,834 --> 01:45:10,569
that exists on the internet,
when people are really,

2143
01:45:10,570 --> 01:45:11,970
get really, really worked up,

2144
01:45:11,971 --> 01:45:13,839
<i>is something that</i>

2145
01:45:13,840 --> 01:45:17,041
<i>the Siskel and Ebert show
helped to seed.</i>

2146
01:45:17,042 --> 01:45:20,579
<i>It follows from Roger's
understanding of criticism,</i>

2147
01:45:20,580 --> 01:45:22,447
<i>which is it's
a mode of conversation.</i>

2148
01:45:22,448 --> 01:45:23,949
<i>It's the public square.</i>

2149
01:45:23,950 --> 01:45:25,984
<i>Golden: This is allowing
your fans to access</i>

2150
01:45:25,985 --> 01:45:28,954
this database of your reviews
going back 1967

2151
01:45:28,955 --> 01:45:32,659
<i>that has never been available
in this form before.</i>

2152
01:45:33,259 --> 01:45:34,960
<i>Computerized voice:
When I am writing,</i>

2153
01:45:34,961 --> 01:45:37,133
<i>I am the same person
I always was.</i>

2154
01:45:40,133 --> 01:45:44,469
<i>Roger: In April 2008, I
wrote my first blog entry,</i>

2155
01:45:44,470 --> 01:45:45,804
<i>and began this current</i>

2156
01:45:45,805 --> 01:45:48,140
<i>and probably final stage
of my life.</i>

2157
01:45:48,141 --> 01:45:51,576
<i>My blog became my voice,
my outlet,</i>

2158
01:45:51,577 --> 01:45:55,045
<i>my social media in a way
I couldn't have dreamed of.</i>

2159
01:45:55,046 --> 01:45:59,751
<i>Into it, I poured my regrets,
desires and memories.</i>

2160
01:45:59,752 --> 01:46:04,089
<i>Most people choose to write
a blog, I needed to.</i>

2161
01:46:04,090 --> 01:46:07,091
<i>Computerized voice: Racism
was ingrained in daily life.</i>

2162
01:46:07,092 --> 01:46:09,895
<i>It wasn't the overt racism
of the South,</i>

2163
01:46:09,896 --> 01:46:11,830
<i>but more like
the pervading background</i>

2164
01:46:11,831 --> 01:46:14,166
<i>against which we lived.
We were here...</i>

2165
01:46:14,167 --> 01:46:17,068
<i>And I've never
held a handgun in my life.</i>

2166
01:46:17,069 --> 01:46:20,037
<i>The theory is that
gun ownership makes us safer,</i>

2167
01:46:20,038 --> 01:46:23,475
<i>that doesn't seem
to be working out for us.</i>

2168
01:46:23,476 --> 01:46:26,111
<i>The body count rises.</i>

2169
01:46:26,112 --> 01:46:29,781
<i>Nack: He took all of that
energy he put into television,</i>

2170
01:46:29,782 --> 01:46:32,117
and he transferred it
to his blog,

2171
01:46:32,118 --> 01:46:34,686
and the internet,
and to his movie reviews,

2172
01:46:34,687 --> 01:46:37,560
and wrote better
than he ever had in his life.

2173
01:46:40,560 --> 01:46:43,094
<i>Man's voice:
Bless these boys.</i>

2174
01:46:43,095 --> 01:46:47,632
<i>( computerized voice )</i>

2175
01:46:47,633 --> 01:46:51,570
<i>I don't know when a film
has connected more immediately</i>

2176
01:46:51,571 --> 01:46:53,738
<i>with my own personal experience.</i>

2177
01:46:53,739 --> 01:46:56,578
<i>That's how you grow up.</i>

2178
01:46:58,578 --> 01:46:59,978
<i>...surrounded by the realms</i>

2179
01:46:59,979 --> 01:47:02,217
<i>of unimaginable time and space.</i>

2180
01:47:03,901 --> 01:47:06,251
<i>Corliss: We are now seeing
the polymathic genius</i>

2181
01:47:06,252 --> 01:47:11,223
<i>that those of us
who knew Roger always saw.</i>

2182
01:47:11,224 --> 01:47:13,758
His voice was stilled,

2183
01:47:13,759 --> 01:47:16,127
but of course
he's talking more than ever.

2184
01:47:16,128 --> 01:47:18,930
<i>( jazz music playing )</i>

2185
01:47:18,931 --> 01:47:22,167
<i>Computerized voice: In the past
25 years, I have probably seen</i>

2186
01:47:22,168 --> 01:47:25,537
<i>ten thousand movies, and
reviewed six thousand of them.</i>

2187
01:47:25,538 --> 01:47:28,206
<i>- She threw them there.
- Man: I understand, but why?</i>

2188
01:47:28,207 --> 01:47:31,743
<i>I have forgotten
most of them, I hope.</i>

2189
01:47:31,744 --> 01:47:34,549
<i>( orchestra flourishing on TV )</i>

2190
01:47:36,549 --> 01:47:41,520
<i>Roger: But I remember
those worth remembering.</i>

2191
01:47:41,521 --> 01:47:45,156
<i>And they are
on the same shelf in my mind.</i>

2192
01:47:45,157 --> 01:47:47,559
<i>Look at a movie
that a lot of people love...</i>

2193
01:47:47,560 --> 01:47:48,994
Match me, Sydney.

2194
01:47:48,995 --> 01:47:51,062
<i>...and you'll find
something profound...</i>

2195
01:47:51,063 --> 01:47:52,764
( speaks French )

2196
01:47:52,765 --> 01:47:54,866
<i>...no matter how silly
the film may seem.</i>

2197
01:47:54,867 --> 01:47:58,570
( band playing rock music )

2198
01:47:58,571 --> 01:48:02,040
- Sing!
- ♪ Oh, worry me! ♪

2199
01:48:02,041 --> 01:48:04,910
<i>What I miss though,
is the wonder.</i>

2200
01:48:04,911 --> 01:48:06,978
Open the pod bay doors, Hal.

2201
01:48:06,979 --> 01:48:09,915
<i>People my age can remember
walking into a movie palace...</i>

2202
01:48:09,916 --> 01:48:11,316
<i>Hal:
I'm sorry, Dave.</i>

2203
01:48:11,317 --> 01:48:12,918
<i>...when the ceiling
was far overhead...</i>

2204
01:48:13,019 --> 01:48:14,619
<i>Hal:
I'm afraid I can't do that.</i>

2205
01:48:14,620 --> 01:48:17,188
<i>...balconies reached
way into the shadows.</i>

2206
01:48:17,189 --> 01:48:19,624
<i>We remember the sound
of a thousand people</i>

2207
01:48:19,625 --> 01:48:21,259
<i>laughing all at once,</i>

2208
01:48:21,260 --> 01:48:23,562
<i>and screens
the size of billboards,</i>

2209
01:48:23,563 --> 01:48:27,032
<i>so every seat in the house
was a good seat.</i>

2210
01:48:27,033 --> 01:48:30,802
<i>"I lost it at the movies,"
Pauline Kael said,</i>

2211
01:48:30,803 --> 01:48:33,972
<i>and we all knew
just what she meant.</i>

2212
01:48:33,973 --> 01:48:35,907
<i>Man:
Charles Foster Kane.</i>

2213
01:48:35,908 --> 01:48:38,180
<i>( dramatic theme music playing )</i>

2214
01:48:41,180 --> 01:48:43,430
<i>James: Only two days after
he'd returned home,</i>

2215
01:48:44,015 --> 01:48:47,652
<i>Roger was readmitted
to the hospital with pneumonia.</i>

2216
01:48:47,653 --> 01:48:51,055
<i>Chaz thought this was a brief
if frustrating setback,</i>

2217
01:48:51,056 --> 01:48:53,792
<i>and so Roger and I resumed
our email interview</i>

2218
01:48:53,793 --> 01:48:55,059
<i>with the plan to film him</i>

2219
01:48:55,060 --> 01:48:57,362
<i>as soon as
he returned home again.</i>

2220
01:48:57,363 --> 01:49:00,599
<i>Roger was energetic
and answered questions</i>

2221
01:49:00,600 --> 01:49:03,101
<i>about a variety of subjects.</i>

2222
01:49:03,102 --> 01:49:07,037
<i>Computerized voice: My favorite places
in the city are the used bookstores.</i>

2223
01:49:07,038 --> 01:49:09,841
<i>You can't get me out of one.</i>

2224
01:49:09,842 --> 01:49:12,844
<i>I love
what I call Formica Diners.</i>

2225
01:49:12,845 --> 01:49:15,814
<i>Those standard places
