2226
01:49:15,815 --> 01:49:18,984
<i>and breakfast 24 hours a day.</i>

2227
01:49:18,985 --> 01:49:21,653
<i>Everything
about the University Club.</i>

2228
01:49:21,654 --> 01:49:24,656
<i>James: I asked about one of his
most controversial reviews</i>

2229
01:49:24,657 --> 01:49:27,058
<i>for "Blue Velvet",
and his moral indignation</i>

2230
01:49:27,059 --> 01:49:28,793
<i>of director David Lynch.</i>

2231
01:49:28,794 --> 01:49:30,996
But he asked Isabella Rossellini
in this movie

2232
01:49:30,997 --> 01:49:33,098
to be undressed
and humiliated on the screen...

2233
01:49:33,099 --> 01:49:36,134
<i>Computerized voice: It seems true
that I have an inbred moral code,</i>

2234
01:49:36,135 --> 01:49:37,969
<i>and that when it is violated,</i>

2235
01:49:37,970 --> 01:49:41,406
<i>I ask myself
if the violation is justified.</i>

2236
01:49:41,407 --> 01:49:44,142
<i>Rossellini's discomfort
seems so obvious</i>

2237
01:49:44,143 --> 01:49:46,778
<i>and palpable that I cringed.</i>

2238
01:49:46,779 --> 01:49:48,813
<i>Drama holds a mirror up to life,</i>

2239
01:49:48,814 --> 01:49:51,383
<i>but needn't reproduce it.</i>

2240
01:49:51,384 --> 01:49:55,423
<i>James: Attempts to film Roger in
